Why is availability_zone required when using 2.77?

If we look at 2.56 where you can specify a requested destination host for cold migration:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/4e9d2244799fb285f75056f9120201aaa408a765/nova/api/openstack/compute/schemas/migrate_server.py#L23

The schema is such that you can do something like:

{
    'migrate': null
}

for backward compatibility, or:

{
    'migrate': {
        'host': 'myhost'
    }
}

Now I remember when we did 2.73 the schema started matching the 2.56 pattern but was changed to be a bit more strict:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/4e9d2244799fb285f75056f9120201aaa408a765/nova/api/openstack/compute/schemas/lock_server.py#L19

Meaning you can do:

{
   'lock': null
}

or

{
    'lock': {
        'locked_reason': 'something'
    }
}

But you can't do:

{
    'lock': {
        'locked_reason': null
    }
}

or

{
    'lock': {
        'locked_reason': ''
    }
}

Which are allowed with 2.56. So I think we should probably follow the 2.73 pattern.

